<big><b>THE ROMAN CIVILIZATION</b></big>

The Ancient Romans built one of the most powerful civilizations in history.

It started in the city of Rome, in present-day Italy, more than 2,000 years ago.

The Roman Empire expanded across Europe, Africa, and Asia.


<big><b>Roman Government</b></big>

Rome was first a kingdom, then a republic, and later an empire.

The Romans created a strong system of government.

Examples:

• Senators helped make laws
• Consuls led the government
• Emperors ruled the empire


<big><b>Roman Roads</b></big>

The Romans built thousands of kilometers of roads.

These roads helped the army, trade, and communication.

Examples:

• Soldiers moved quickly across the empire
• Goods were transported between cities
• Cities became connected


<big><b>Roman Buildings</b></big>

Romans were famous for their architecture.

They built strong structures using stone, brick, and concrete.

Examples:

• The Colosseum hosted gladiator games
• Aqueducts brought water to cities
• Temples were built for their gods


<big><b>Daily Life</b></big>

Roman society had different social classes.

People worked in many different jobs:

• Farmers
• Soldiers
• Traders
• Engineers

Examples:

• Wealthy families lived in large houses called villas
• Poor people lived in small apartments
• Public baths were important social places


<big><b>Roman Religion</b></big>

Romans believed in many gods.

Some important gods were:

• Jupiter – king of the gods
• Mars – god of war
• Venus – goddess of love

Later, Christianity became very important in the empire.


<big><b>Roman Army</b></big>

The Roman army was very powerful and well organized.

It helped the empire expand and stay strong.

Examples:

• Soldiers trained every day
• They used shields and short swords
• Forts were built across the empire


<big><b>Interesting Facts</b></big>

• Latin was the Roman language
• Many modern languages come from Latin
• Roman laws influenced modern legal systems
• The Roman Empire lasted over 1,000 years


